Temperature and Precipitation 1960-2014

Data

Tell which data we use (see the readme file) and for which purpose.

We used the percipitation and temperature dataset and analyzed specifically North America. In using this data, we are able to visualize the trends of the weather from 1960, 1986, and 2014.

Temperature

comment the results. Do the temperature patterns look reasonable? Do you see major differences between years?

There doesnt really seem to be too much of a difference between years except for areas near Alaska getting cooler and parts of the central US getting warmer. Additionally as you look at areas that are further south in North America, the stronger the intensity of red there is. For example, if you look at Canada, the colors observed are green and an orangeish. However, if you examine Mexico, the colors are green and a deep red.

Precipitation

insert your precipitation images here comment the results.

Do the precipitation patterns look reasonable? Do you see major differences between years?

There seems to be (on average) a lot more percipitation across North America in 1986 than in 1960. In 2019, there seems to be less percipitation than 1986 (on average). Additionally, the plot seems to have stronger percipitation around the coasts of North America, rather than the more central areas.
